  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Archdiocese of Lilongwe Palliative Care Project</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The overall aim of this project is to equip a total of 197 volunteers with a sound knowledge in basic nursing, how to organise village savings and loans schemes, and how to provide sensitive and culturally appropriate psychosocial and palliative care, in Malawi. It is anticipated that 1,200 people with chronic illness and people leaving with HIV and AIDS will benefit from this project.  The project will implement the following activities in addressing the critical challenges the communities are encountering:
- Village savings and loan schemes (VSL) 
- Palliative care training 
- Psychosocial training 
- Technical support of all structures involved in the implementation of the programme remains a critical component of the programme and this requires a motor vehicle, should resources be made available.</narrative>
  </description>
